<TEXT>
cancer rates are decliningbut the disease remains 
the second leading cause of premature death in the united states 
according to the centers for disease control 
in 1985 the last year for which statistics were available 
cancer accounted for the loss of 195 million years of potential 
life americans would have had if they had lived to age 65 the 
atlantabased cdc said thursday in its weekly report 
only injuries with a loss of 22 million years ranked higher 
the cdc counts years of potential life lost to various causes 
as a way of measuring premature mortality using age 65 as a 
statistical benchmark the actual life expectancy is higher 
since 1968 the mortality rate from cancer for americans under 55 
has dropped significantly from 43 deaths per 100000 people in that 
age group in 1968 to 35 in 1985 over that same time the annual 
rate of potential life years lost has fallen as well from 1074 
years lost among every 100000 people to 926 
all of that leads to some guarded optimism that cancer rates 
in younger people are in fact declining said dr richard 
rothenberg a cdc cancer specialist 
in the 1985 figures the highest rate for potentiallife years 
lost to cancer was among black males at 1208 years per 100000 
such people following were white males 949 black females 877 
and white females 841 
but while proportionately fewer people are dying early of cancer 
the population is growing particularly baby boomers now ages 
2442 thus cancers toll in the total number of years of 
potential life lost has remained virtually constant for two 
decades the cdc noted 
understanding the basis and public health implications of this 
decline in cancer death rates requires further investigation 
the cdc said noting that such efforts should include study of 
cancer incidence and survival among younger americans 
additionally rothenberg said researchers have another concern 
with improvements in other areas of medicine such as treatment of 
cardiovascular disease americans are living longer so the cancer 
rate for people over 65 is increasing 
it sounds simplistic but it means theyre living long enough 
to get cancer he said 
