president reagan and soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev signed 
the inf treaty in washington on dec 7 1987 the agreement which 
bans mediumrange nuclear missiles took effect in june salt lake 
county and votkinsk are the only two permanent inspection sites 
named in the treaty 
what were doing today is starting a joint cultural tradition 
with the celebration of the signing of the treaty that brings you 
here to utah james szatkowski us site commander said during 
the party 
as many as 30 soviet inspectors will serve two and threemonth 
duty tours for the next 13 years in salt lake county under terms of 
the treaty 
theres certainly a sense of history in what were about here 
and a sense of pioneering in the area of peace szatkowski said 
i think were all proud to be a part of this exciting time in 
international history 
