middle east 
and it was at a news conference on june 11 1987 in venice 
italy that he said he thought the dollar could decline further 
within reason at a time when his administration was trying to 
keep it from sliding at all 
the first reagan white house news conference like most in the 
early days of his administration was held in a workmanlike 
auditorium in the old executive office building next door to the 
white house 
in mid1982 the sessions were moved to the more ornate if less 
comfortable east room on the glittering state floor of the executive 
residence 
a further refinement was instituted in 1984 instead of 
addressing reporters with his back to the east wall of the room 
reagan switched to the west side giving him a chance to make an 
entrance down a hallway visible through an open door 
our people just got tired of seeing me in the same set he 
cracked at the time 
thursday night the entrance was even more dramatic than usual 
because of christmas decorating at the white house reagan could not 
pop out of the blue room as he usually does but had to enter the 
hall from the red room which is farther away 
despite the changes in trappings however it was the flow of the 
news that set the tone of the news conferences from turmoil in 
central america and lebanon to the irancontra arms and money 
scandal and the battles over the budget deficit 
at that first news conference there were seven questions about 
relations with iran thursday night there was one 
in january 1981 there was one question about relations with the 
soviet union thursday night there were five 
the news conference also showed there is one thing reporters have 
learned in eight years of trying to pin reagan down to specifics 
nearly every reporter thursday night took advantage of the 
opportunity to ask a followup question 
at the first conference in 1981 none of them did 
