<TEXT>
china on friday honored the 40th anniversary of 
the united nations declaration of human rights although questions 
remain about this nations commitment to such concepts 
fei xiaotong a wellknown sociologist was quoted by the 
official xinhua news agency as saying that china actively supports 
the development of human rights 
fei speaking at a forum to commemorate the un declaration 
said chinas constitution guarantees individual rights including 
freedom of religion and equality before the law 
he noted however that the struggle for human rights should 
concentrate not on individual freedoms but on fighting colonialism 
racism and foreign invasion 
the report was the latest in a series of articles in the official 
press stressing chinas position that collective rights are more 
important than individual liberties 
a xinhua report this week said china believes that civil 
liberties rights of minorities and women belong to the internal 
affairs of a country and advised other countries not to meddle in 
those questions 
an article in the nov 28 issue of beijing review an official 
weekly softpedaled discussion of individual liberties human 
rights it said were a key part in the efforts of third world 
countries to establish a new economic order 
by pushing such a policy china can justify both its criticism of 
apartheid in south africa and its rejection of accusations about its 
policies in tibet or its oneparty state 
it is no good to force one countrys standards on another 
fridays xinhua report said interference in a countrys internal 
affairs on the pretext of human rights should be strictly 
forbidden 
western human rights groups have persisted in criticizing chinas 
record 
in february the washingtonbased group asia watch said chinese 
authorities tortured tibetan activists seeking independence from 
china and performed forced abortions on members of minority groups 
proindependence tibetans have rioted twice in the past two 
years leaving dozens dead in lhasa the regions capital 
the asia watch report quoted one tibetan as saying if one 
speaks forcefully if one gives an account of tibet as being 
independent they apply cattle prods 
earlier this year the us congress also criticized china for 
its actions in tibet 
an amnesty international report in april accused china of denying 
prisoners access to lawyers or their families in earlier years the 
