la coupole the landmark left bank restaurant where 
struggling young artists like chagall and picasso traded their 
paintings for hot meals reopened friday after eight months of 
renovations restoring its 1920s decor 
la coupole is more than a restaurant its an institution 
said jeanpaul bucher la coupoles new owner 
bucher president of the groupe flo chain of brasseries known for 
good food fair prices and quick service said the coupole 
machine still had to be oiled and would get off to a slow start 
