chess long into the night 
the postworld war ii generation of existentialists made la 
couple their haunt until his death in 1980 jeanpaul sartre 
lunched there daily with simone de beauvoir 
the coupoles main dining room is a classified historical 
monument and renovations of its vintage 1920s decor cost an 
estimated 5 million 
on hand for the inaugural lunch of foie gras scallops chicken 
fricasee and an orange mousse cake washed down with vintage medoc 
wines was rene lafon 91 the coupoles original owner 
entering the restaurant i was very happy to find my coupole 
he said 
the famed 32 pillars wrapped with original but mostly unsigned 
