to be a pandoras box 
under the cracking plaster workmen found a type of emerald green 
stone that looked like marble though it was once the rage of paris 
and still adorns the facade of some of the citys loveliest 
buildings repairs were no easy matter this manmade stone is no 
longer manufactured 
the paintings themselves had been darkened beyond recognition by 
60 years of smoke and cooking grime they are now more resplendent 
