over the issue of robinsons right to be granted bail 
moore said robinson would be required to put up 500000 in the 
form of a surety bond plus 500000 in the form of a personal 
recognizance bond moore added that robinson would be required to 
remain in greenville county until his trial scheduled to begin jan 
16 
a personal recognizance bond means a defendant is liable for the 
amount of the bond but he does not have to offer documentation that 
he has the money 
moore also agreed friday that the murder charges against robinson 
and the charges involving the attack on the murder witness should be 
tried separately to avoid prejudice 
