<TEXT>
the grandson of leon trotsky sat in the room 
where one of stalins assassins killed the old revolutionary with an 
ax and pondered how far the new more enlightened kremlin would go 
toward making amends 
if glasnost wants to have authenticity it must recognize 
the proper place of leon trotsky in history esteban volkow 
bronstein said using the word denoting the more open soviet 
policies of mikhail s gorbachev 
the latest sign of change came dec 6 when volkow received 
permission to visit his halfsister alexandra who is dying of 
cancer in moscow he has not been to the soviet union or seen his 
sister in 57 years and learned only last month that she was alive 
its all part of gorbachevs policy volkow said and trotsky 
has been emerging slowly from the dark cave of soviet history 
since glasnost began 
for 50 or 60 years the russian public has been conditioned to 
think of him as almost the devil his grandson said you cant 
change black to white in one day 
leon trotsky born lev davidovich bronstein in 1879 was among 
the most popular leaders of the 1917 bolshevik revolution 
commander of the red army commissar for war and foreign affairs 
the right hand of lenin after losing a power struggle with josef 
stalin he became a nonperson 
stalin exiled him in 1929 and trotskys name was stricken from 
soviet history photographs and film were doctored to erase his 
image real and imagined followers were hunted down and imprisoned 
or killed 
trotskys road ended on a summer afternoon in at his desk in the 
modest house in coyoacan in those days was a quiet village 
coyoacan is enveloped by the smog of mexico city now but in the 
house itself little has change since the assassin entered it aug 
20 1940 with a mountaineers ice ax 
it has no plaques polished display cases or uniformed guards 
but there is a caretaker to greet visitors he answers the bell 
shows them through the rooms and hands them the guest book to sign 
there was a terrible solitude an emptiness here in the 
house volkow said remembering the years after the assassination 
he was born in the soviet union to trotskys daughter zina and now 
is 62 a semiretired chemical engineer 
trotskys house always has attracted a few soviet visitors he 
said but more have come in the past year or so 
they are opening windows in russia volkow said they are 
turning on the light there is a freshness 
glasnost has not altered trotskys official status but his name 
sometimes is mentioned publicly and the soviet supreme court 
rehabilitated a son volkows stepuncle sergei sedov who died in a 
stalin purge 
in september the communist party newspaper pravda called trotsky 
an enemy of stalin rather than an enemy of socialism and the 
revolution 
i believe that his heroic struggle almost alone against one 
of the most terrible the bloodiest tyrannies in history is the 
stage of his life that is going to have the most historical 
importance volkow said 
a quiet river that ran behind trotskys house two generations ago 
has become a stream of vehicles belching fumes on a freeway but in 
the shadowed rooms behind thick walls time seems congealed 
its curious he didnt live here long but he impregnated 
the house with his presence the grandsom said 
beside the reading lamp the dictaphone waits next to books in 
french german russian spanish and english on hitler capitalism 
italian fascism colonialism british trade unionism 
the bloodstains on trotskys chair have faded but bullet holes 
from an earlier assassination attempt still pock the bedroom walls 
he had the windows shuttered with steel and the gateway bricked 
up after the attack may 24 1940 by mexican stalinists with machine 
guns 
three months later a stalinist agent who had insinuated himself 
into the trotsky circle attacked with the ice ax when volkow then 
14 entered the room his grandfather lay on the floor bleeding his 
wife at his side 
the assassin spent 20 years in prison but his identity never was 
confirmed he was thought to be a spaniard ramon del rio mercader 
but also was known as jacques mornard and frank jackson 
volkow said trotsky treated each day after the may attack as a 
bonus every morning after he got up he would say another day of 
life natalia another day of life 
natalia sedov trotskys second wife lived in the house for more 
than 20 years after the assassination she died in paris in 1962 
in the garden a simple gray stone monument carved with a hammer 
and sickle encloses the ashes of trotsky and natalia 
a red flag flutters overhead 
