affirmed a decision that the merger violated a 1984 agreement 
between warner and its largest stockholder christcraft industries 
inc a broadcasting and manufacturing company 
at issue in the case are lorimars televison stations 
chriscraft claimed in a suit filed in july that because lorimar 
owned six stations the merger violated a 4yearold pact 
prohibiting warner from owning any tv station so long as it owned 25 
percent or more of chriscrafts bhc inc broadcasting subsidiary 
warner acquired a 425 percent stake in bhc in 1984 in exchange 
for chris craft getting 23 percent of warners voting stock 
the appeals court upheld a a ruling that said warner could not 
acquire any lorimar stock until the tv stations were sold or it 
reduced its stake in bhc 
