the european economic community said friday that 
a ban on the imports of hormonetreated meat from the united states 
will go into effect next month 
the ban implementation of which was postponed for one year at 
the request of the united states could provoke a trade war with 
washington 
eec spokesman nicolas wegter also said the 12nation eec only 
would agree to international arbitration of the dispute with the 
united states if consumerrelated arguments as well as scientific 
ones are taken into account 
the ban legislated by the eec which goes into effect jan 1 
would affect 170 million of us meat exports this does not 
include about 72 million of horsemeat which is not treated with 
hormones 
eec and us negotiators were expected to have an opportunity to 
discuss possible solutions to the dispute when they met here this 
week for a ministerial conference of the general agreement on 
tariffs and trade 
but a useec clash over support for farmers prevented the 
discussion from taking place the matter will also not be taken up 
at a bilateral meeting of ministers taking place in brussels friday 
because the us and eec agriculture negotiators had to stay in 
montreal longer than expected and did not get to belgium in time 
we dont care what the americans want for their consumers 
said wegter our legislation goes into effect and we will apply 
it 
a european parliament investigation of reports that european 
farmers violate the legislation and treat their animals with 
hormones will not affect implementation of the ban he said 
the council of the gatt which oversees implementation of the 
1947 treaty regulating world trade is scheduled to meet dec 20 to 
consider a us request for establishing an arbitration pnel 
wegter said the eec would only accept the arbitration panel if it 
doesnt rely just on scientific arguments but also on 
consumerrelated and other arguments he said most eec members 
already had legislated bans on hormonetreated meat and they 
think its good for their consumers 
the united states insists that hormones used on animals do not 
