european buyers is very acceptable 
there is no health problem involved as we see it he said 
after meeting with officials of the 12nation common market trade 
bloc 
in montreal a spokesman for the european community nico wegter 
said the ban would take effect jan 1 as scheduled 
we dont care what the americans want for their consumers 
wegter said our legislation goes into effect and we will apply 
it 
the eec wants to ban for health reasons all meat from animals 
treated with growth hormones late last year it agreed to delay 
implementation of the prohibition until 1989 
the united states had threatened to take retaliatory action 
against the ban it maintains that the use of hormones to fatten 
animals a common practice among american farmers is not a health 
risk 
an estimated 170 million in us meat exports would be affected 
by the ban 
shultz said the value of meat exports to the eec is small 
compared to this years estimated 166 billion twoway trade between 
the united states and the trading bloc but he said its large 
to the people involved 
he acknowledged a difference of opinion with the community but 
said we think were right 
