<TEXT>
here is a capsule description of an unbundled 
stock unit a new type of security developed by shearson lehman 
hutton inc 
four major companies american express co sara lee corp 
pfizer inc and dow chemical co have announced plans subject to 
federal review to exchange up to 56 billion of their stock for 
unbundled stock units 
the new securities consist of 
a 30year bond that pays interest equal to the current stock 
dividend and carrying a face value payable in 2019 higher than the 
current stock price 
under the preliminary proposal for instance american expresss 
bond would pay 84 cents a year in interest and have a face value of 
75 american express stock was trading at 2687 the last trading 
day before the proposal 
a share of preferred stock that will entitle the holder to any 
dividends declared by the company in excess of the current dividend 
for american express that would be anything above 84 cents a year 
the preferred share could also be redeemed in 2019 for a nominal 
price expected to be 2 
a stock appreciation certificate that will give the holder the 
right to purchase for cash a share of the companys stock in 2019 
for the principal amount of the bond plus the preferred share in 
the american express example that would be 77 
it is expected that subject to appropriate approvals the 
unbundled stock unit each of its parts and a security that combines 
the preferred share and the stock appreciation certificate would be 
traded on the new york stock exchange just as the companys stock 
</TEXT>
