mead which is based in dayton ohio already has an electronic 
publishing unit mead data central that accounted for about 231 
million of the parent companys 42 billion in revenue in 1987 
among mead centrals services are the lexis database that 
compiles legal news and the nexis service that offers general and 
financial news to 200000 users in the united states and overseas 
this important acquisition is a further reflection of mead data 
centrals long term commitment to expand the services and products 
it offers the legal community said burnell r roberts meads 
chairman and chief executive 
